3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method to generate plans that are robust to imperfect perception of the environment, which is a problem in artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The optimization procedure proposed in the paper involves linked inputs and has analytical gradients, which are techniques used in machine learning. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although the paper does not explicitly deal with computer vision, the problem of generating plans that are robust to imperfect perception of the environment can be seen as a problem in computer vision.
